article_title: Police seek help locating diabetic woman last seen in southeast Dallas
article_text:
Dallas police are asking the public to help find a woman last seen Thursday in a southeast Dallas neighborhood.

Francisca Gomez, who is diabetic and needs insulin, was last seen walking away from the 8100 block of Bambi Street about 12 p.m. Thursday, police said in a news release issued this morning.

She was wearing a pink jacket and gray jogging pants. She didn’t take her medicine, ID, phone or her purse with her, police said.

Police believe she could have had a medical emergency because of her medical condition.

Anyone with information is asked to call 911 or Dallas police at 214-671-4268.
